  "text": "Start the session, but make the warm-up the decider. Your data really is clean: recovery is 70%, HRV is 63 ms against a 30-day average of 60.7, resting heart rate is 56 bpm right on your usual 56.5, and you slept 426 minutes, about 7.1 hours. Yesterday's 31-minute row was modest, load 13.4, so there's no hidden physical debt these numbers are missing. Flatness with green data is usually mental fatigue, low fuel, or plain mood, and those often lift once you're moving; that's why the fairest test is doing the full warm-up and the first easy block before judging. If the flatness burns off, continue as planned. If you still feel empty after warming up, downgrade to an easy session rather than grinding; motivation that low is worth respecting even when physiology isn't the cause.",
